 founder and a liberal benefactor of the University of California at Berkeley where he is memorialized by the Sather Gate and Sather Tower (the Campanile), three endowed professorships, and more recently the Peder Sather Center for Advanced Study. Karin Sveen, one of Norway’s most accomplished writers, pieces together a story yet untold—a beautifully crafted biography based on her dedicated search for scraps of information. The result gives readers a look at the life of a successful entrepreneur and a leading California patron who engaged in public education on all levels; supported Abraham Lincoln; and worked to give emancipated slaves housing, schooling, and employment after the Civil War. His legacy and vivid persona and the frontier city of his time are brought to life with interesting anecdotes of many famous people— General William T. Sherman, Walt Whitman, Mark Twain, Robert Louis Stevenson, the Norwegian violinist Ole Bull, and above all, his close friend Anthony J. Drexel, legendary Philadelphia financier and one of the founders of Wall Street.    aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBusinessmenzCaliforniazSan Francisco. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  aamerican civil war.  abanking house.  aberkeley.  abiographical.  abiography.  acalifornia patron.  acalifornia.  acareer.  acharity.  aemancipated slaves.  aengaging.  afamily.  afamous people.  ahistorical.  ahistory.  ahumanitarian.  ainteresting anecdotes.  aliberal benefactor.  alife changes.  alifetime.  amoney and banking.  amoney and power.  amoney.  anew york.  anorway.  apeder sather.  aphilanthropy.  apower and wealth.  apublic education.  asuccessful entrepreneur.  auniversity of california at berkeley.08iTitle is part of eBo